explanation: [0-0] Two young women are standing on a grassy field, each carrying a baby in a front-facing carrier. The baby held by the woman on the left is holding a string of colorful beads. In front of each woman, there is a green metal water pump. They place their hands near the pump handles, and a red bucket is placed at the water outlet. In the distance behind them is a high mountain with many houses at its base.

[0-8] They make a motion of pressing the water pump handles, but their hands do not actually touch the handles. They repeatedly squat and stand, and with their movements, the pump handles move up and down accordingly. The water below is drawn into the pump pipes. After repeating this action three times, water is seen flowing out of the pump in front of the woman on the right, flowing into the red bucket placed below. However, the pump on the left does not produce water. They then stop their actions, and the woman on the right bends down to pick up her bucket. The woman on the left looks at her with a puzzled expression and then spreads her right hand. The woman on the right then walks away with her bucket.
